July 19 2022 Update:

- Added code to resize the PowerShell console. If the PowerShell console buffer size / window size was too small, the output from many of the commands would be truncated to the point that the information would not be useful.
- Reworked the way registry values are exported. Now uses 'reg.exe export <path\to\reg\hive>' as it gives better output and is more useful.
- Included export of 32-bit Veeam registry values (HKLM\SOFTWARE\WOW6432Node\Veeam)

February 27 2024 Update:
- Overhaul of event viewer log export to CSV code to drastically speed up overall execution time.
- Removed forced resizing of console and instead modified the default Out-File width.
- Removed copy of %ProgramData%\Veeam\Backup if the script was executed on the VBR server as this could potentially be a massive folder.
- Added extensionless file to exported zip archive letting the engineer know if this script was ran on the VBR server as this is not the typical use case.
- Redirected various output to null that wasn't intended to be sent to console.

February 9 2026 Update:
- Added user prompt for whether or not to include Security events in the log collection (defaults to no).

June 10 2026 Update:
- Added collection of FLTMC.exe output (registered Filter Manager minifilter drivers) to FLTMC.txt.
- Added -IncludeSecurityEvents and -Force parameters so the script can run unattended/remotely (via Invoke-Command). GUI prompts are now only shown in interactive sessions; non-interactive sessions are driven entirely by parameters.
- Replaced Win32_Product query for installed software with registry uninstall key enumeration. Querying Win32_Product forces Windows Installer consistency checks on every installed MSI package which can trigger spontaneous repairs, high CPU usage, and floods the Application event log being collected.
- Replaced Get-WmiObject with Get-CimInstance throughout (WMI cmdlets are removed in PowerShell 7).
- Added fallbacks for cmdlets not available before Windows Server 2012 / Windows 8: Win32_Volume (CIM) for Get-Volume, 'netsh advfirewall' for Get-NetFirewallProfile, and an explanatory note when Get-NetAdapterBinding is unavailable.
- Each collection step is now individually error-handled and failures are recorded to CollectionErrors.log inside the archive, replacing the global suppression of all errors.
- Replaced legacy Shell.Application COM zip fallback (~140 lines) with .NET ZipFile compression, which is available on all supported PowerShell versions and has no file size limitations. This also fixes exported event logs not being included in the archive on PowerShell 4.0.
- Fixed Write-Console being called before it was defined in the PowerShell ISE check.
- Fixed only the last named SQL instance being collected when multiple named instances are running.
- Fixed invalid registry value name detection flagging any name containing a space instead of only leading/trailing whitespace.
- SQL permissions report is now buffered and written once instead of re-opening the log file for every line.
- Event log CSV export now streams directly to disk to reduce memory usage.
- The collected log folder is only deleted after verifying the zip archive was created successfully.
- Removed cosmetic Start-Sleep delays (saves ~30 seconds per run).
- Miscellaneous cleanup: temp path derived from SystemDrive, $env:COMPUTERNAME instead of hostname.exe, directories created before transcription starts.
- Introduced script versioning (2.0). The version is printed at startup and recorded in the Execution.log transcript inside the archive so support can identify which script revision produced a bundle.
- Added -OutputDirectory parameter to redirect the collected bundle to an alternate location (e.g. when the default volume is low on disk space).
- Added hypervisor detection and guest tools collection (hypervisor_info.log): VMware Tools version and service status, Hyper-V Integration Services version and vmic* service status, or Nutanix Guest Tools version.
- Added collection of installed Windows updates/hotfixes (installed_hotfixes.log).
- Tabular outputs (installed software, services, volume info, local accounts, 'File and Printer Sharing' status) are now exported as CSV instead of fixed-width text so they can be sorted and filtered in a spreadsheet. Additional columns were added now that width is no longer a constraint (e.g. service short name, start mode and binary path; software install location).
- Added a triage summary file (!_SUMMARY.txt) at the root of the archive. It surfaces facts extracted from the collected data: VSS writers not in a stable state, non-default VSS providers, key service states (VSS, COM+ Event System, CryptSvc, WMI, SQLWriter when SQL is present, Veeam services), volumes below free space thresholds, minifilter drivers not shipped in-box with Windows, pending reboot indicators, SCHANNEL protocol customizations, and any failed collection steps. The summary is advisory (facts, not verdicts); checks that cannot be parsed (e.g. localized vssadmin output on non-English OSes) are flagged for manual review rather than reporting an all-clear. VSS provider identification uses locale-independent provider IDs so third-party providers are still detected on non-English systems.
